use me well."</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=qwik>Qwik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/8/01 10:02:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yet another beginning...</span><hr size=1> &quot;tis a pleasure Liandriana Sedai ... i go by Qwik Ta`veren .. seems as though we already have something in common m'lady &quot; he grins knowing she would figure out their shared interest. &quot;As for the Militia i cannot say i approve of their ways, if only i were here sooner to aid you though tis quite obvious you are not a woman who requires assistance though i would be quite saddened if you deny'd me the honor.&quot; smiling brightly Qwik walked closer still minding the hulking mass of earth guarding her. &quot;Its been quite an evening for the both of us Liandriana Sedai could i convince you to walk with me to the inn ?&quot; &quot;looks as though you could use something to take the edge off ... my treat of course, mayhaps we could talk .... being alone for the past months has taken a toll on me and i do not wish to sit alone ... and mabey we can catch up with your friend on our way ? &quot;<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/8/01 6:25:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yet another beginning...</span><hr size=1> Hearing the sound of a dwarven voice bellow behind her, Casidy turned towards the sound.<br>
<br>
"Dalmanth, is it REALLY you?" Casidy popped up from her chair, turning to Jzonn she spoke softly "if you will excuse me, I know this dwarven fellow. If you should get the chance before you retire for the evening would you look in on Scaly, he should be resting in the room upstairs." Without waiting for a reply to her request, Casidy turned her attentions back to the dwarf at hand.<br>
<br>
Casidy ran up to Dalmanth and threw her arms around him. "Let me get that drink for you friend," Motioning for one of the serving girls to bring over the mug of ale that Vanlaan had purchased. <br>
<br>
Turning back to Dalmanth, Casidy smiled and winked, "it is late and this tired fellow," indicating Vanlaan with her hands as she spoke "was on his way up stairs for rest."<br>
<br>
"Perhaps you can entertain a wee bard, and tell me the tale of how you managed to make your way here. I had heard you were killed in battle in the Karanas." Casidy's voice had that lyric quality of a bard, to calm and return order to an otherwise stressful situation. <br>
<br>
In one statement, she had both dismissed Vanlaan to return to his room, and smothered the fiery rage brewing in Dalmanth. Whatever his concern it would wait until the morning, there would be no more battles here this evening. The tension in the room began to dissipate.<br>
